| **H2_Coherence** | MC-SCI scores will differentiate between institutional and populist discourse. | ‚ùå **FAILED** | Test could not be executed. The `test_hypothesis_H2_coherence_differences` task failed due to missing component scores. |
| **H3_Architecture** | The v7.0 gasket architecture will successfully process 2-document analysis with Raw Analysis Log processing. | ‚ùå **REJECTED** | The experiment successfully tested the architecture and found it to be non-functional. It failed to extract any scorable dimensions, halting all analysis. |

### **Detailed Statistical Analysis & Evidence Integration**
No quantitative statistical analysis was possible. The sections below diagnose the failure by contrasting the expected output with the actual outcome, using curated evidence to illustrate what the system failed to process.

#### **Dimensional Score Analysis: A Systemic Failure**
The core of the CAF v7.0 is the generation of dimensional scores. The `calculate_derived_metrics` task failed because none of these scores were extracted. The evidence demonstrates that the source material was not the cause of this failure.

For instance, John McCain's speech contained a powerful appeal to national unity and optimism, a textbook example of the **Hope** dimension: *"I urge all Americans who supported me to join me in not just congratulating him, but offering our next president our good will and earnest effort to find ways to come together..."* [1]. It also included a clear expression of respect for the historic nature of the election for a specific demographic, a core component of the **Dignity** dimension [4].

Similarly, Bernie Sanders' speech provided strong, quantifiable rhetoric on the **Justice** axis. His call to action against perceived inequity‚Äî*"We will not accept the richest guy in the world...all so that they could give over a trillion dollars in tax breaks to the wealthiest 1%."* [2]‚Äîis a clear instance of the Justice dimension. The same speech also contained powerful language of **Resentment**, targeting a perceived out-of-touch elite: *"These guys have no sense of what goes on in the real world. They live in another planet."* [3].

The failure to generate `justice_score` and `resentment_score` from this text prevented not only the individual assessment but also the calculation of `justice_resentment_tension`, a key metric for understanding populist rhetoric within the CAF framework.

